body:
@JoakimSoderberg I faced the same issue. The `option` you passed is not a pointer as expected by the [go-flags](https://github.com/jessevdk/go-flags) lib, so it panics [here](https://github.com/jessevdk/go-flags/blob/master/group.go#L378).

And this leads to a dead lock in the generated `Shutdown()` function in `server.go` called by the `defer` in `main.go` because the shutdown message is sent to a nil channel (channel axioms:  [A send to a nil channel blocks forever](https://dave.cheney.net/2014/03/19/channel-axioms))

In `main.go`:
```go
func main() {
   ...
   defer server.Shutdown()
   ...
```

in `server.go`:
```go
// Shutdown server and clean up resources
func (s *Server) Shutdown() error {
	if atomic.LoadInt32(&s.shuttingDown) != 0 {
		s.Logf("already shutting down")
		return nil
	}
	s.shutdown <- struct{}{}
	return nil
}
```

If you add `&` in front of the `struct` it works fine.
